## File Organization

### Recommended Structure
```
project-root/
├── src/                    # Source code
│   ├── core/              # Core business logic
│   ├── utils/             # Utility functions
│   ├── services/          # Service layer
│   └── models/            # Data models
├── tests/                 # Test files
│   ├── unit/             # Unit tests
│   ├── integration/      # Integration tests
│   └── e2e/              # End-to-end tests
├── docs/                  # Documentation
│   ├── ARCHITECTURE.md   # Architecture documentation
│   └── COMMON_MISTAKES.md # Known issues and mistakes
├── scripts/               # Build and utility scripts
├── .claude/              # Claude Code configuration
│   ├── agents/           # Custom agents
│   └── commands/         # Custom commands
├── README.md             # Project overview and setup
├── CLAUDE.md             # This file
└── package.json          # Dependencies (if applicable)
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Files**: Use consistent casing (kebab-case, snake_case, or camelCase based on language)
- **Directories**: Use lowercase with hyphens or underscores
- **Tests**: Name test files clearly (e.g., `user.test.js`, `test_user.py`)
- **Constants**: Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- **Classes**: Use PascalCase for class names
- **Functions/Variables**: Use camelCase or snake_case based on language conventions

